What makes something feel “alive”

Not substance—behavior.

A living system typically has:

* structure (it’s not random)
* variation (it’s not static)
* feedback (it responds / resolves)
* memory (motifs, recurrence)
* adaptation (it evolves over time)

Music hits all of those:

* rhythm = structure in time
* melody = variation
* harmony = feedback (tension ↔ resolution)
* motifs = memory
* improvisation / progression = adaptation

So your intuition is right, just slightly reframed:

Music simulates life dynamics using sound as the medium.

